title: Maluku Islands
summary: The Maluku Islands or the Moluccas (/məˈlʌkəz/) (Molukken) are an archipelago to the East of Indonesia. Tectonically they are located on the Halmahera Plate within the Molucca Sea Collision Zone. Geographically they are located east of Sulawesi, west of New Guinea, and north and east of Timor. Lying within Wallacea (mostly east of the biogeographical Weber Line), the Maluku islands have been considered part of both Asia and Oceania.
